<section class="faq" data-screen-label="11 FAQ" data-comment-anchor="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq__inner">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Common questions</span>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:16px">Before you book.</h2>
        <p class="section-intro" style="margin-top:24px">If you're weighing up whether we're the right fit, these are the questions we get asked most.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__list reveal" style="--d:120">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-item__btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do you execute the marketing for me?</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-item__panel"><div class="faq-item__panel-inner">No, and that's deliberate. We're not a typical agency. We build the strategy, set the systems, and guide you and your team to implement it consistently. That model scales without making us a bottleneck, and it leaves you with the capability.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-item__btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I need a fractional CMO or a marketing agency?</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-item__panel"><div class="faq-item__panel-inner">If you need someone to execute campaigns, you can hire an agency or other implementation suppliers. If you need someone to lead your marketing function, connect it to revenue, and hold your team accountable, that's a fractional CMO. Most growth-focused businesses need leadership before execution.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-item__btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>How long until marketing starts showing results?</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-item__panel"><div class="faq-item__panel-inner">Quick wins like better positioning, clearer messaging and fixed gaps usually show in 30 to 60 days. Qualified leads from consistent content and outbound activity typically take 3 to 6 months. Compounding momentum kicks in around month 9 to 12. Marketing rewards consistency, not bursts. We don't make guarantees; results depend on consistent, well-executed implementation, and that's what we're here to lead.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-item__btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>How do you use AI in your work?</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-item__panel"><div class="faq-item__panel-inner">AI is one of the tools we use to help clients create better content faster, not a substitute for strategy or human judgement. We're human-first. AI is brought in where it improves quality or speed, never where it would dilute brand voice or replace strategic thinking.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-item__btn" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>How is HMC different from a typical agency?</span>
            <span class="faq-item__icon"><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg></span>
          </button>
